The paper deals with a computer vision problem of estimating 3D pose from 2D projections, which is a common topic in the computer vision community. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel adversarial framework to learn the 3D structure from 2D projections, which involves training a generator and a discriminator network. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with human pose estimation, which is a sub-topic of graphics and visualization. Therefore, cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on a dataset, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
